---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CopyBlock from '../components/CopyBlock.astro';
const GH = 'https://github.com/cargopete/nuthatch';
---
<Layout
  path="/install"
  title="Install Nuthatch"
  description="Install Nuthatch: shell script, cargo, Homebrew, or Docker for scaled mode. With checksum and signature verification."
>
  <section class="page">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Install</p>
      <h1>Get Nuthatch running.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Embedded mode is a single static binary with no external services. Pick whichever
        route you trust. Every one lands you at the same place: <code>nuthatch init</code>,
        then <code>nuthatch dev</code>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="ih">Shell script</h2>
      <p>Detects your platform, downloads the matching static binary, verifies its checksum, and puts it on your <code>PATH</code>.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="curl -fsSL https://nuthatch-indexer.com/install.sh | sh" size="lg" />
      <p class="note">
        Piping to a shell asks for trust. Read it first:
        <a href="https://github.com/cargopete/nuthatch-frontend/blob/main/public/install.sh" rel="noopener">the script is short and on GitHub</a>,
        or download it, read it, then run it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="ih">Cargo</h2>
      <p>If you have a Rust toolchain, build from source. No prebuilt binary in the trust path.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="cargo install nuthatch" />

      <h2 class="ih">Homebrew</h2>
      <p>macOS and Linuxbrew.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="brew install nuthatch" />

      <h2 class="ih">Docker — scaled mode</h2>
      <p>
        Embedded mode needs no Docker. Reach for the compose stack only for scaled mode,
        where Postgres replaces the embedded hot store and DataFusion federates hot and cold
        behind one SQL surface. Same crates, one storage flag.
      </p>
      <CopyBlock command="curl -fsSL https://nuthatch-indexer.com/docker-compose.yml -o docker-compose.yml && docker compose up" prompt={true} />

      <h2 class="ih">First run</h2>
      <p>Point it at a contract and go. Public RPC defaults; no key required.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="nuthatch init 0xA0b86991c6218b36c1d19D4a2e9Eb0cE3606eB48 --chain mainnet" />
      <CopyBlock command="nuthatch dev" />
      <p class="note">
        <code>init</code> writes a config and the resolved ABI. <code>dev</code> follows the
        tip and serves SQL, GraphQL, and MCP on one local endpoint.
      </p>

      <hr class="divider ih-div" />

      <h2 class="ih">Verify what you downloaded</h2>
      <p>
        Binaries ship with a SHA-256 checksum file and a detached signature. The shell
        script checks the sum for you; do it yourself for the other routes.
      </p>
      <CopyBlock command="sha256sum -c nuthatch-<version>-<target>.tar.gz.sha256" prompt={true} />
      <p>Then verify the signature against the release signing key:</p>
      <CopyBlock command="gpg --verify nuthatch-<version>-<target>.tar.gz.sig" prompt={true} />
      <div class="keybox">
        <span class="keybox-label">Release signing key</span>
        <code class="keybox-id"><!-- TODO: real GPG key id at first tagged release -->0xNUTHATCH0000000000000000000000000000000</code>
        <p class="keybox-note">Placeholder until the first signed release. The key id and fingerprint will be published here and in the repository.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="backlink"><a href={GH} rel="noopener">Source, docs, and issues on GitHub →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page { padding-block: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem) clamp(4rem, 8vw, 6rem); }
  .page h1 { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .lede { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .ih { margin-top: 2.8rem; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-size: 1.35rem; }
  .ih-div { margin-block: 2.8rem 0; }
  .page p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page :global(.copyblock) { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .note { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-faint); }
  .keybox { margin-top: 1rem; background: var(--bg-elev); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem; }
  .keybox-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-faint); }
  .keybox-id { display: block; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--accent-ink); word-break: break-all; }
  .keybox-note { margin: 0.6rem 0 0; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  .backlink { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .backlink a { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
